---
const problems = [
  {
    number: "01",
    title: "Your compliance team is blocking AI adoption",
    description:
      "Every time someone on your team uses ChatGPT or Claude with internal documents, customer data, or proprietary code, that information is sent to servers you don't control and can't audit. One compliance question you can't answer — or one data incident — and the project gets shut down.",
  },
  {
    number: "02",
    title: "You're one pricing change away from a budget problem",
    description:
      "Build on a public AI API and you're subject to their pricing changes, rate limits, and deprecation schedule. Every model update is a potential breaking change. Every price hike hits your budget directly. And when a provider decides to compete in your market, your AI infrastructure belongs to them.",
  },
  {
    number: "03",
    title: "Building it yourself takes months you don't have",
    description:
      "Assembling a production-grade self-hosted AI stack from scratch — model server, document database, workflow automation, secure access, observability — is a 3–6 month engineering project. Most teams don't have the specialized expertise to do it, or the runway to spend it on infrastructure.",
  },
];
---

<section id="problem" class="border-t border-deep-700/50 py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Why most companies get stuck on AI</h2>
      <p>
        Every option forces a compromise between speed, security, and control.
        OpenSAS is the first path that doesn't.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {problems.map((problem) => (
        <div class="card problem-card group">
          <div class="mb-4 font-mono text-4xl font-bold text-deep-700 leading-none select-none group-hover:text-accent/20 transition-colors duration-300">
            {problem.number}
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white leading-snug">{problem.title}</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-deep-400">{problem.description}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
